---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import {
	LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE,
	LEGAL_ROUTES,
	PUBLISHER,
	mailtoHref,
	EMAILS,
} from '../config/legal';
---

<Layout
	title="DMCA & Copyright Policy — Ultiplay"
	description="How to submit a DMCA takedown notice or counter-notification to Ultiplay LLC, and the current status of our Designated Copyright Agent."
>
	<Nav />

	<main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
		<header>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-fuchsia-300">Legal</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl">
				DMCA &amp; Copyright Policy
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">
				Effective: {LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE} &nbsp;·&nbsp;
				<a href={LEGAL_ROUTES.index} class="underline hover:text-slate-300">Back to legal index</a>
			</p>
		</header>

		<div class="mt-12 space-y-10 text-slate-300">
			<section>
				<p>
					{PUBLISHER.legalName} respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects
					users of the Services to do the same. We respond to clear notices of alleged copyright
					infringement that comply with the U.S. Digital Millennium Copyright Act
					(<strong class="text-white">"DMCA"</strong>), 17 U.S.C. § 512.
				</p>
				<div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-5 text-sm text-slate-300">
					<p>
						<strong class="text-white">Scope.</strong> Ultiplay is primarily a desktop application
						that plays media stored on or accessed by the user's own device. The desktop
						application does <strong class="text-white">not</strong> host or store user-supplied
						media content on Ultiplay servers. The only files {PUBLISHER.legalName} stores on
						your behalf are (a) update artifacts that we publish ourselves and (b) support bundles
						that you explicitly upload (which contain logs/settings, not media). Accordingly, the
						bulk of the § 512 safe harbor regime is not implicated by the Software. If you
						believe content
						<strong class="text-white"> on the
						<a href="/" class="text-fuchsia-300 underline hover:text-fuchsia-200">ultiplay.net</a>
						website itself</strong> infringes your copyright, use the procedure below.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">1. Notification of alleged infringement (DMCA takedown notice)</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					To submit a DMCA notice, send a written communication to our Designated Copyright Agent
					containing <strong class="text-white">all</strong> of the following:
				</p>
				<ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>
						A physical or electronic signature of the copyright owner or a person authorized to
						act on the owner's behalf.
					</li>
					<li>
						Identification of the copyrighted work claimed to have been infringed (or, if
						multiple, a representative list).
					</li>
					<li>
						Identification of the material claimed to be infringing or to be the subject of
						infringing activity, including its URL or other location reasonably sufficient for us
						to find it.
					</li>
					<li>Your contact information (full name, mailing address, telephone number, and email).</li>
					<li>
						A statement that you have a <strong class="text-white">good-faith belief</strong> that
						use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the copyright
						owner, its agent, or the law.
					</li>
					<li>
						A statement, <strong class="text-white">under penalty of perjury</strong>, that the
						information in your notification is accurate and that you are the copyright owner or
						authorized to act on the owner's behalf.
					</li>
				</ol>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">2. Designated Copyright Agent</h2>
				<div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-amber-300/30 bg-amber-300/5 p-5 text-sm">
					<p class="text-amber-100/90">
						<strong class="text-amber-100">Status:</strong> As of {LEGAL_EFFECTIVE_DATE},
						{` `}{PUBLISHER.legalName} has not yet completed registration of a Designated Agent
						with the U.S. Copyright Office at
						<a href="https://dmca.copyright.gov" rel="noopener" class="underline hover:text-amber-50">
							dmca.copyright.gov
						</a>. Until that registration is completed, DMCA safe harbor under 17 U.S.C. § 512(c)
						is <strong>not</strong> being claimed for any user-generated content. Because the
						Software does not host user-generated media, this gap is intentional for the initial
						release; {PUBLISHER.legalName} will register a Designated Agent before introducing
						any feature that stores or makes available media on behalf of third parties.
					</p>
				</div>
				<p class="mt-4">Pending formal registration, copyright-related correspondence may be sent to:</p>
				<address class="mt-3 not-italic rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-4 font-mono text-xs text-slate-200">
					{PUBLISHER.legalName}<br />
					Attn: Copyright / DMCA<br />
					{PUBLISHER.addressLine1}<br />
					{PUBLISHER.city}, {PUBLISHER.region} {PUBLISHER.postal}<br />
					{PUBLISHER.country}<br />
					Email:
					<a href={mailtoHref('dmca')} class="text-fuchsia-300 underline hover:text-fuchsia-200">{EMAILS.dmca}</a>
				</address>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">3. Counter-notification</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					If you believe content was removed in error or misidentified, you may submit a
					counter-notification containing:
				</p>
				<ol class="mt-3 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>Your physical or electronic signature.</li>
					<li>
						Identification of the material removed and the location where it appeared before
						removal.
					</li>
					<li>
						A statement, <strong class="text-white">under penalty of perjury</strong>, that you
						have a good-faith belief that the material was removed as a result of mistake or
						misidentification.
					</li>
					<li>
						Your name, address, and telephone number; consent to the jurisdiction of the U.S.
						District Court for the District of Colorado (or, if outside the U.S., the federal
						district where {PUBLISHER.legalName} is located); and a statement that you will
						accept service of process from the original complainant.
					</li>
				</ol>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">4. Repeat infringers</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					We will, in appropriate circumstances and at our discretion, terminate the accounts,
					licenses, and access of users who are determined to be repeat infringers.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">5. Misrepresentations</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					Knowingly material misrepresentations in either a notification or counter-notification
					may subject the submitting party to liability for damages under 17 U.S.C. § 512(f).
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</Layout>
